{"at":"2026-07-22T08:02:07.747Z","type":"agent.message","threadId":"pi-root-019f88d7-d364-73c4-a4eb-ca15474d82cf","itemId":"pi-root-019f88d7-d364-73c4-a4eb-ca15474d82cf:message:4","message":"Run:\n\n```bash\npi config\n```\n\nFind the Watchdog package/extension and toggle its **extension** resource off. That only disables Pi loading it; it does **not** uninstall the npm package.\n\n- Press `Tab` in `pi config` to switch global vs project-local scope.\n- Restart Pi afterward (or try `/reload`).\n\nYou can re-enable it later from the same menu."}
